Shinsei Bank Appoints Ex-Goldman’s Makihara as Outside Director

-- B y   S h i g e r u   S a t o
-- 
2011-05-12T09:27:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/shinsei-bank-appoints-ex-goldman-s-makihara-as-outside-director.html
Shinsei Bank Ltd. (8303) , the Japanese
lender partly owned by J. Christopher Flowers, named Jun Makihara, a former  Goldman Sachs Group Inc. (GS)  executive, as an
outside director.  The appointment is subject to approval by shareholders at
the Tokyo-based lender’s annual general meeting scheduled for
June 22, it said in a statement filed to the Tokyo Stock
Exchange today. Makihara currently is chairman of Neoteny Co., a
Japanese Internet investment firm.  Makihara, 53, had worked at Goldman Sachs in New York and
Tokyo for almost two decades and was once a managing director
and branch manager of the U.S. company’s Tokyo office. He is a
graduate from Harvard Business School.  After two years of losses, Shinsei today posted net income
of 42.7 billion yen in the year ended March.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shigeru Sato in  Tokyo  at 
 ssato10@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chitra Somayaji at 
 csomayaji@bloomberg.net . 